## Escalation cadence (from observed audit patterns)

| Reminder # | Days overdue | Tone | Action |
|---|---|---|---|
| #1 | 0–7 days past due | Polite confirmation request | Send |
| #2 | 8–21 days | Direct, asking for status | Send + Ashley CC'd |
| #3 | 22–45 days | Firm, requesting expected pay date | Send + Ashley CC'd + log in tracker |
| #4 | 46–90 days | Escalate, ask for call | Send + suggest CFO Day call |
| #5+ | 90+ days | Operator must personally call | Skip skill — operator handles via phone |

Real example from audit: `FW: (Reminder-5-) Tüpraş Online - Account Reconciliation 03/2026` — by reminder #5, Maaz is forwarding the original chain to Ashley for tracking, not just emailing again.

